Rodimus and Kup follow Perseus dpwn the hall after the escaped Predacon.

Kup: If I get a firing solution I&#39;m taking it.

Kraftlos &lt;kraftlos@...&gt; wrote:                                  Salveo and the troopers rush to the first partition which separated the command center hallway from the more open entrance area.  He walked up to the wall and pulled open a hatch, revealing a manual crank for the doors.  As they turn the crank, the door slowly lowers into the closed position. 

&quot;He wont be getting out this way!&quot; shouted one of the troopers confidently as they moved to seal off the armory next.

Meanwhile...

Having been given orders to return to base, he decided that he had better find a way out of the base. 

&quot;AGGGGGGGG!&quot; he shouted as the door to the secret exit shuddered.  After a second and third blow, the door was off and was blown about 50 feet from the door frame.

As Trelos took off down the corridor, Perseus finally managed to get the door open to the lower section.  He could immediately see that Trelos had taken the not-so-secret exit-way.  With no power to the forcefields, it was a simple matter of running.  He looked into the security office and saw the guard laying unconscious or perhaps dead. 

&quot;Perseus to all personnel.  The prisoner appears to have escaped out the lower exit.  We need to catch him before he reaches the city.&quot; he said into the radio, then taking off down the passageway.  &quot;Kenzo, we have one guard in need of attention, he appears to have been attacked by the prisoner.&quot; 


